    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 997.1 Carrera is powered by a mid-mounted 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six, featuring VarioCam Plus for optimized valve timing across the rev range. The power is managed by a precise G97 6-speed manual gearbox, delivering torque through a rear-wheel-drive configuration. The suspension architecture remains tight, utilizing a subframe-mounted multi-link rear setup and MacPherson struts up front for surgical turn-in. Mechanical integrity is prioritized with a documented IMS bearing retrofit and a high-flow water pump to ensure thermal efficiency. The braking system retains its factory-spec four-piston monobloc aluminum calipers, providing excellent modulation and heat dissipation. This is a mechanically sound example with a clean bore-scope report and consistent compression across all cylinders, ready for spirited canyon carving or track-day duty.",
